{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So I was privileged to train in transplantation"},{"time":5000,"text":"under two great surgical pioneers:"},{"time":7000,"text":"Thomas Starzl,"},{"time":9000,"text":"who performed the world's first successful liver transplant"},{"time":12000,"text":"in 1967,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and Sir Roy Calne,"},{"time":16000,"text":"who performed the first liver transplant in the U.K."},{"time":19000,"text":"in the following year."},{"time":22000,"text":"I returned to Singapore"},{"time":24000,"text":"and, in 1990,"},{"time":26000,"text":"performed Asia's first successful"},{"time":28000,"text":"cadaveric liver transplant procedure,"},{"time":31000,"text":"but against all odds."},{"time":34000,"text":"Now when I look back,"},{"time":36000,"text":"the transplant was actually the easiest part."},{"time":40000,"text":"Next, raising the money to fund the procedure."},{"time":44000,"text":"But perhaps the most challenging part"},{"time":48000,"text":"was to convince the regulators --"},{"time":50000,"text":"a matter which was debated in the parliament --"},{"time":54000,"text":"that a young female surgeon"},{"time":56000,"text":"be allowed the opportunity"},{"time":58000,"text":"to pioneer for her country."},{"time":61000,"text":"But 20 years on,"},{"time":63000,"text":"my patient, Surinder,"},{"time":65000,"text":"is Asia's longest surviving"},{"time":67000,"text":"cadaveric liver transplant to date."},{"time":70000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":74000,"text":"And perhaps more important,"},{"time":77000,"text":"I am the proud godmother"},{"time":79000,"text":"to her 14 year-old son."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"But not all patients on the transplant wait list"},{"time":87000,"text":"are so fortunate."},{"time":89000,"text":"The truth is,"},{"time":91000,"text":"there are just simply not enough donor organs"},{"time":93000,"text":"to go around."},{"time":95000,"text":"As the demand for donor organs"},{"time":97000,"text":"continues to rise,"},{"time":99000,"text":"in large part due to the aging population,"},{"time":102000,"text":"the supply has remained relatively constant."},{"time":106000,"text":"In the United States alone,"},{"time":108000,"text":"100,000 men, women and children"},{"time":112000,"text":"are on the waiting list for donor organs,"},{"time":115000,"text":"and more than a dozen die each day"},{"time":118000,"text":"because of a lack of donor organs."},{"time":121000,"text":"The transplant community"},{"time":123000,"text":"has actively campaigned in organ donation."},{"time":126000,"text":"And the gift of life"},{"time":128000,"text":"has been extended"},{"time":130000,"text":"from brain-dead donors"},{"time":132000,"text":"to living, related donors --"},{"time":134000,"text":"relatives who might donate an organ"},{"time":137000,"text":"or a part of an organ,"},{"time":139000,"text":"like a split liver graft,"},{"time":141000,"text":"to a relative or loved one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"But as there was still a dire shortage of donor organs,"},{"time":147000,"text":"the gift of life was then extended"},{"time":149000,"text":"from living, related donors"},{"time":151000,"text":"to now living, unrelated donors."},{"time":154000,"text":"And this then has given rise"},{"time":157000,"text":"to unprecedented and unexpected"},{"time":160000,"text":"moral controversy."},{"time":163000,"text":"How can one distinguish"},{"time":166000,"text":"a donation that is voluntary and altruistic"},{"time":169000,"text":"from one that is forced or coerced"},{"time":172000,"text":"from, for example,"},{"time":174000,"text":"a submissive spouse, an in-law,"},{"time":177000,"text":"a servant, a slave,"},{"time":179000,"text":"an employee?"},{"time":181000,"text":"Where and how can we draw the line?"},{"time":185000,"text":"In my part of the world,"},{"time":188000,"text":"too many people live below the poverty line."},{"time":191000,"text":"And in some areas,"},{"time":193000,"text":"the commercial gifting of an organ"},{"time":195000,"text":"in exchange for monetary reward"},{"time":198000,"text":"has led to a flourishing trade"},{"time":200000,"text":"in living, unrelated donors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"Shortly after I performed the first liver transplant,"},{"time":207000,"text":"I received my next assignment,"},{"time":209000,"text":"and that was to go to the prisons"},{"time":212000,"text":"to harvest organs"},{"time":214000,"text":"from executed prisoners."},{"time":217000,"text":"I was also pregnant at the time."},{"time":220000,"text":"Pregnancies are meant"},{"time":222000,"text":"to be happy and fulfilling moments"},{"time":225000,"text":"in any woman's life."},{"time":227000,"text":"But my joyful period"},{"time":229000,"text":"was marred by solemn and morbid thoughts --"},{"time":234000,"text":"thoughts of walking through"},{"time":236000,"text":"the prison's high-security death row,"},{"time":239000,"text":"as this was the only route"},{"time":241000,"text":"to take me to the makeshift operating room."},{"time":245000,"text":"And at each time,"},{"time":247000,"text":"I would feel the chilling stares"},{"time":250000,"text":"of condemned prisoners' eyes follow me."},{"time":254000,"text":"And for two years,"},{"time":256000,"text":"I struggled with the dilemma"},{"time":258000,"text":"of waking up at 4:30 am"},{"time":260000,"text":"on a Friday morning,"},{"time":262000,"text":"driving to the prison,"},{"time":264000,"text":"getting down, gloved and scrubbed,"},{"time":266000,"text":"ready to receive the body"},{"time":269000,"text":"of an executed prisoner,"},{"time":271000,"text":"remove the organs"},{"time":273000,"text":"and then transport these organs"},{"time":275000,"text":"to the recipient hospital"},{"time":277000,"text":"and then graft the gift of life"},{"time":280000,"text":"to a recipient the same afternoon."},{"time":283000,"text":"No doubt, I was informed,"},{"time":285000,"text":"the consent had been obtained."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"But, in my life,"},{"time":293000,"text":"the one fulfilling skill that I had"},{"time":298000,"text":"was now invoking feelings of conflict --"},{"time":302000,"text":"conflict ranging"},{"time":304000,"text":"from extreme sorrow and doubt at dawn"},{"time":308000,"text":"to celebratory joy"},{"time":310000,"text":"at engrafting the gift of life at dusk."},{"time":314000,"text":"In my team,"},{"time":316000,"text":"the lives of one or two of my colleagues"},{"time":319000,"text":"were tainted by this experience."},{"time":322000,"text":"Some of us may have been sublimated,"},{"time":325000,"text":"but really none of us remained the same."},{"time":329000,"text":"I was troubled"},{"time":332000,"text":"that the retrieval of organs from executed prisoners"},{"time":336000,"text":"was at least as morally controversial"},{"time":339000,"text":"as the harvesting of stem cells"},{"time":341000,"text":"from human embryos."},{"time":344000,"text":"And in my mind,"},{"time":346000,"text":"I realized as a surgical pioneer"},{"time":349000,"text":"that the purpose of my position of influence"},{"time":352000,"text":"was surely to speak up"},{"time":354000,"text":"for those who have no influence."},{"time":357000,"text":"It made me wonder"},{"time":359000,"text":"if there could be a better way --"},{"time":361000,"text":"a way to circumvent death"},{"time":364000,"text":"and yet deliver the gift of life"},{"time":366000,"text":"that might exponentially impact"},{"time":369000,"text":"millions of patients worldwide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"Now just about that time,"},{"time":375000,"text":"the practice of surgery evolved"},{"time":377000,"text":"from big to small,"},{"time":379000,"text":"from wide open incisions"},{"time":381000,"text":"to keyhole procedures,"},{"time":383000,"text":"tiny incisions."},{"time":386000,"text":"And in transplantation, concepts shifted"},{"time":389000,"text":"from whole organs to cells."},{"time":392000,"text":"In 1988, at the University of Minnesota,"},{"time":395000,"text":"I participated in a small series"},{"time":398000,"text":"of whole organ pancreas transplants."},{"time":401000,"text":"I witnessed the technical difficulty."},{"time":404000,"text":"And this inspired in my mind"},{"time":406000,"text":"a shift from transplanting whole organs"},{"time":410000,"text":"to perhaps transplanting cells."},{"time":412000,"text":"I thought to myself,"},{"time":414000,"text":"why not take the individual cells"},{"time":417000,"text":"out of the pancreas --"},{"time":419000,"text":"the cells that secrete insulin to cure diabetes --"},{"time":422000,"text":"and transplant these cells? --"},{"time":425000,"text":"technically a much simpler procedure"},{"time":427000,"text":"than having to grapple with the complexities"},{"time":430000,"text":"of transplanting a whole organ."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433000,"text":"And at that time,"},{"time":435000,"text":"stem cell research"},{"time":437000,"text":"had gained momentum,"},{"time":439000,"text":"following the isolation of the world's first"},{"time":442000,"text":"human embryonic stem cells"},{"time":444000,"text":"in the 1990s."},{"time":447000,"text":"The observation that stem cells, as master cells,"},{"time":450000,"text":"could give rise"},{"time":452000,"text":"to a whole variety of different cell types --"},{"time":454000,"text":"heart cells, liver cells,"},{"time":456000,"text":"pancreatic islet cells --"},{"time":458000,"text":"captured the attention of the media"},{"time":461000,"text":"and the imagination of the public."},{"time":464000,"text":"I too was fascinated"},{"time":466000,"text":"by this new and disruptive cell technology,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and this inspired a shift in my mindset,"},{"time":472000,"text":"from transplanting whole organs"},{"time":474000,"text":"to transplanting cells."},{"time":477000,"text":"And I focused my research on stem cells"},{"time":480000,"text":"as a possible source"},{"time":482000,"text":"for cell transplants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485000,"text":"Today we realize"},{"time":487000,"text":"that there are many different types of stem cells."},{"time":490000,"text":"Embryonic stem cells"},{"time":492000,"text":"have occupied center stage,"},{"time":494000,"text":"chiefly because of their pluripotency --"},{"time":498000,"text":"that is their ease in differentiating"},{"time":501000,"text":"into a variety of different cell types."},{"time":505000,"text":"But the moral controversy"},{"time":508000,"text":"surrounding embryonic stem cells --"},{"time":511000,"text":"the fact that these cells are derived"},{"time":513000,"text":"from five-day old human embryos --"},{"time":516000,"text":"has encouraged research"},{"time":518000,"text":"into other types of stem cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"Now to the ridicule of my colleagues,"},{"time":525000,"text":"I inspired my lab"},{"time":527000,"text":"to focus on what I thought"},{"time":530000,"text":"was the most non-controversial source of stem cells,"},{"time":534000,"text":"adipose tissue, or fat, yes fat --"},{"time":537000,"text":"nowadays available in abundant supply --"},{"time":541000,"text":"you and I, I think, would be very happy to get rid of anyway."},{"time":546000,"text":"Fat-derived stem cells"},{"time":548000,"text":"are adult stem cells."},{"time":550000,"text":"And adult stem cells"},{"time":552000,"text":"are found in you and me --"},{"time":554000,"text":"in our blood, in our bone marrow,"},{"time":556000,"text":"in our fat, our skin and other organs."},{"time":559000,"text":"And as it turns out,"},{"time":561000,"text":"fat is one of the best sources"},{"time":563000,"text":"of adult stem cells."},{"time":565000,"text":"But adult stem cells"},{"time":567000,"text":"are not embryonic stem cells."},{"time":570000,"text":"And here is the limitation:"},{"time":572000,"text":"adult stem cells are mature cells,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and, like mature human beings,"},{"time":578000,"text":"these cells are more restricted in their thought"},{"time":581000,"text":"and more restricted in their behavior"},{"time":584000,"text":"and are unable to give rise"},{"time":586000,"text":"to the wide variety of specialized cell types,"},{"time":589000,"text":"as embryonic stem cells [can]."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"But in 2007,"},{"time":594000,"text":"two remarkable individuals,"},{"time":597000,"text":"Shinya Yamanaka of Japan"},{"time":599000,"text":"and Jamie Thomson of the United States,"},{"time":602000,"text":"made an astounding discovery."},{"time":605000,"text":"They discovered"},{"time":607000,"text":"that adult cells, taken from you and me,"},{"time":610000,"text":"could be reprogrammed"},{"time":613000,"text":"back into embryonic-like cells,"},{"time":615000,"text":"which they termed IPS cells,"},{"time":618000,"text":"or induced pluripotent stem cells."},{"time":623000,"text":"And so guess what,"},{"time":625000,"text":"scientists around the world and in the labs"},{"time":628000,"text":"are racing"},{"time":630000,"text":"to convert aging adult cells --"},{"time":633000,"text":"aging adult cells from you and me --"},{"time":635000,"text":"they are racing to reprogram these cells"},{"time":638000,"text":"back into more useful IPS cells."},{"time":643000,"text":"And in our lab,"},{"time":645000,"text":"we are focused on taking fat"},{"time":647000,"text":"and reprogramming"},{"time":649000,"text":"mounds of fat"},{"time":651000,"text":"into fountains of youthful cells --"},{"time":655000,"text":"cells that we may use"},{"time":657000,"text":"to then form other,"},{"time":659000,"text":"more specialized, cells,"},{"time":661000,"text":"which one day may be used as cell transplants."},{"time":665000,"text":"If this research is successful,"},{"time":668000,"text":"it may then reduce the need"},{"time":671000,"text":"to research and sacrifice"},{"time":673000,"text":"human embryos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677000,"text":"Indeed, there is a lot of hype, but also hope"},{"time":680000,"text":"that the promise of stem cells"},{"time":682000,"text":"will one day provide cures"},{"time":684000,"text":"for a whole range of conditions."},{"time":686000,"text":"Heart disease, stroke, diabetes,"},{"time":689000,"text":"spinal cord injury, muscular dystrophy,"},{"time":691000,"text":"retinal eye diseases --"},{"time":694000,"text":"are any of these conditions"},{"time":696000,"text":"relevant, personally, to you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":699000,"text":"In May 2006,"},{"time":702000,"text":"something horrible happened to me."},{"time":705000,"text":"I was about to start a robotic operation,"},{"time":707000,"text":"but stepping out of the elevator"},{"time":709000,"text":"into the bright and glaring lights of the operating room,"},{"time":712000,"text":"I realized"},{"time":714000,"text":"that my left visual field"},{"time":716000,"text":"was fast collapsing into darkness."},{"time":719000,"text":"Earlier that week,"},{"time":721000,"text":"I had taken a rather hard knock"},{"time":723000,"text":"during late spring skiing -- yes, I fell."},{"time":726000,"text":"And I started to see floaters and stars,"},{"time":728000,"text":"which I casually dismissed"},{"time":730000,"text":"as too much high-altitude sun exposure."},{"time":733000,"text":"What happened to me"},{"time":735000,"text":"might have been catastrophic,"},{"time":737000,"text":"if not for the fact"},{"time":739000,"text":"that I was in reach of good surgical access."},{"time":741000,"text":"And I had my vision restored,"},{"time":743000,"text":"but not before a prolonged period of convalescence --"},{"time":746000,"text":"three months --"},{"time":748000,"text":"in a head down position."},{"time":750000,"text":"This experience"},{"time":752000,"text":"taught me to empathize more with my patients,"},{"time":755000,"text":"and especially those with retinal diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"37 million people worldwide"},{"time":761000,"text":"are blind,"},{"time":763000,"text":"and 127 million more"},{"time":766000,"text":"suffer from impaired vision."},{"time":769000,"text":"Stem cell-derived retinal transplants,"},{"time":772000,"text":"now in a research phase,"},{"time":774000,"text":"may one day restore vision,"},{"time":776000,"text":"or part vision,"},{"time":778000,"text":"to millions of patients with retinal diseases worldwide."},{"time":782000,"text":"Indeed, we live"},{"time":784000,"text":"in both challenging"},{"time":786000,"text":"as well as exciting times."},{"time":790000,"text":"As the world population ages,"},{"time":793000,"text":"scientists are racing"},{"time":795000,"text":"to discover new ways"},{"time":797000,"text":"to enhance the power of the body"},{"time":799000,"text":"to heal itself through stem cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"It is a fact"},{"time":804000,"text":"that when our organs or tissues are injured,"},{"time":807000,"text":"our bone marrow"},{"time":809000,"text":"releases stem cells"},{"time":811000,"text":"into our circulation."},{"time":813000,"text":"And these stem cells"},{"time":815000,"text":"then float in the bloodstream"},{"time":817000,"text":"and hone in to damaged organs"},{"time":820000,"text":"to release growth factors"},{"time":822000,"text":"to repair the damaged tissue."},{"time":824000,"text":"Stem cells may be used as building blocks"},{"time":827000,"text":"to repair damaged scaffolds within our body,"},{"time":831000,"text":"or to provide new liver cells"},{"time":833000,"text":"to repair damaged liver."},{"time":836000,"text":"As we speak, there are 117 or so clinical trials"},{"time":839000,"text":"researching the use of stem cells"},{"time":842000,"text":"for liver diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844000,"text":"What lies ahead?"},{"time":846000,"text":"Heart disease"},{"time":848000,"text":"is the leading cause of death worldwide."},{"time":850000,"text":"1.1 million Americans"},{"time":852000,"text":"suffer heart attacks yearly."},{"time":855000,"text":"4.8 million"},{"time":857000,"text":"suffer cardiac failure."},{"time":859000,"text":"Stem cells may be used"},{"time":861000,"text":"to deliver growth factors"},{"time":863000,"text":"to repair damaged heart muscle"},{"time":865000,"text":"or be differentiated"},{"time":867000,"text":"into heart muscle cells"},{"time":869000,"text":"to restore heart function."},{"time":871000,"text":"There are 170 clinical trials"},{"time":874000,"text":"investigating the role of stem cells in heart disease."},{"time":878000,"text":"While still in a research phase,"},{"time":881000,"text":"stem cells may one day herald"},{"time":884000,"text":"a quantum leap in the field of cardiology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"Stem cells provide hope for new beginnings --"},{"time":891000,"text":"small, incremental steps,"},{"time":894000,"text":"cells rather than organs,"},{"time":897000,"text":"repair rather than replacement."},{"time":900000,"text":"Stem cell therapies"},{"time":903000,"text":"may one day reduce the need for donor organs."},{"time":907000,"text":"Powerful new technologies"},{"time":909000,"text":"always present enigmas."},{"time":911000,"text":"As we speak,"},{"time":913000,"text":"the world's first human embryonic stem cell trial for spinal cord injury"},{"time":916000,"text":"is currently underway"},{"time":918000,"text":"following the USFDA approval."},{"time":921000,"text":"And in the U.K.,"},{"time":923000,"text":"neural stem cells to treat stroke"},{"time":925000,"text":"are being investigated in a phase one trial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"The research success that we celebrate today"},{"time":932000,"text":"has been made possible"},{"time":934000,"text":"by the curiosity and contribution and commitment"},{"time":938000,"text":"of individual scientists"},{"time":940000,"text":"and medical pioneers."},{"time":942000,"text":"Each one has his story."},{"time":945000,"text":"My story has been about my journey"},{"time":948000,"text":"from organs to cells --"},{"time":950000,"text":"a journey through controversy,"},{"time":952000,"text":"inspired by hope --"},{"time":954000,"text":"hope that, as we age,"},{"time":957000,"text":"you and I may one day celebrate longevity"},{"time":960000,"text":"with an improved quality of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}